I hold grudges ... I simply do, because I also really like to prove people WRONG. 🌈

You were happy because your child walked at 1 years old. I am even happier because mine walked at 6 years old. 

Getting to the part where I hold grudges like I'm being paid; 
4 years ago, I spent R5000 cash to take my son to the BEST Peadiatric Neuro Surgeon in the country at St Augustines in Durban ... 
Just to be told that we should "give up, stop trying ...make him comfortable", because he will never reach any milestones. 

A week later he sat up on his own, 2 months later he stood up for the 1st time and started crawling ...

I wasted R5000 if you ask me. 

Then fast forward to 2023. We have been steady, but stagnant, no improvements with the added seizures. 
2 Cysts was found on his brain, which I had to FORCE them to investigate after WRONGLY diagnosing my son with Epilepsy, which I immediately called BULLSHIT. 

I was right (as always). 

In the meeting about a month ago, again when asking the specialist whether my son will ever be able to walk, or be able to improve physically past this point, his answer was IMMEDIATELY no. 

"Nothing we are able to do for him medically will help."

Ok ... So now we have to stick a middle finger to some more people ... Again. 

Today. A month later, on 05/09/2023 we took our 1st SUCCESSFUL steps with our walker, with zero assistance. 

Anyone want to keep telling us we can't do something. 😂🙏
Just a casual Monday ... ✌️

January 2024 is the month of Detox, and leading up to the last few days of December 2023 ... It is honestly the perfect theme.🌈

2023 has been a year, let me tell you. 
Although harder than most, it was the year where I gained the people who matter, care, and truelly have the purest hearts, and - not lost- got rid of, the people only along for the ride when it comes to how much we could give, and how much they could take. 

Detox doesn't only apply to physically getting healthy, getting rid of the bad and unhealthy and inviting the good and fresh ... I think for me, it also mentally means letting go of all the bad in 2023, and allowing the positive to enter in 2024. 🥂

I am excited, and thankful for the lessons learned in 2023, and I actually find myself being happy to leave behind those parasites, to make room for everyone who deserves my 2024. ☀️

I learned that no matter how good my intentions always are and always have been, some slimmy snake somewhere, won't have those same intentions. 
I learned - all too clearly - that the way I was raised, and the values I hold dear, CLEARLY isn't something EVERYONE was taught. 

I also learned that the bad always loses, and always gets rid of itself. 
I learned that bad people, with bad intentions are like a cancer, and it should NEVER be allowed close to you. It should never have any ounce of opportunity to take hold and grow and feed off you. ⚡ Cancer has only ONE job, and it is to get cut off and cut out. 

So ... If YOU were a cancer this year, good riddance. 👏

And to those who filled my cup, even when their own were half empty - I look forward to having you in my new year. ❤️
